					<head>Kabbalah</head>
					<msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85018546" rend="visible">
						<summary>A collection of kabbalistic texts.</summary>
						<textLang mainLang="he"/>
						<msItem rend="visible" class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85018546">
							<locus from="4r" to="7v"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Sefer megilat setarim</title>
							<title xml:lang="he">ספר	מגלת סתרים</title>
							<note>
								<p>Ascribed previously to Moses Maimonides.</p>
								<p>At the end, folio 6v, there are two passages from Sefer ha-Bahir and a short piece on Tetragrammaton.</p>
							</note>
							<author>
								<persName xml:lang="en" key="http://viaf.org/viaf/28526108">Ibn Shimʻon, Joseph ben Judah</persName>
								<persName xml:lang="he" key="http://viaf.org/viaf/28526108">אבן שמעון, יוסף בן יהודה</persName>
							</author>
						</msItem>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="7v" to="9v"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Sefer ha-῾iyun</title>
							<title xml:lang="he">ספר העיון</title>
							<filiation>Cf. the contents of Add MS 15299/XX.</filiation>
							<colophon xml:lang="he">כל זה פרוש חכם מקובל מאבותיו הגדולים מעיר בלדרש. ע"כ מצאתי כתוב בזה הספר השית יזכינו לקרות בו ולהבין סתריו ורמזיו אכי"ר ע"ה <name type="person" role="scribe">דוד נטף</name> יצ"ו".<locus n="9v"/>
							</colophon>
							<note>
								<p>The authorship has been ascribed to Ḥammai Gaon.</p>
							</note>
						</msItem>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="10r" to="29v"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Sha῾are ḳedushah</title>
							<title xml:lang="he">שערי קדושה</title>
							<author>
								<persName xml:lang="en" key="http://viaf.org/viaf/34704971">Vital, Ḥayyim ben Joseph, 1542-1620</persName>
								<persName xml:lang="he" key="http://viaf.org/viaf/34704971">ויטל, חיים בן יוסף</persName>
							</author>
							<note>
								<p>Contains part 4, 3 and a fragments of part 2 of Vital's treatise. The heading states the the manuscripts was copied from the author's handwriting.</p>
								<p>Appended is a piece called Yedi῾at ha-῾arugot, followed by a note on the angles of the 12 planets.</p>
								<p>See also <ref target="Pachter_1976" type="page">404</ref> n. 35.</p>
							</note>
						</msItem>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="30r" to="35r"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Igeret</title>
							<title xml:lang="he">אגרת</title>
							<author>
								<persName xml:lang="en" key="http://viaf.org/viaf/79054878">Abulafia, Abraham ben Samuel, 1240-approximately 1292</persName>
								<persName xml:lang="he" key="http://viaf.org/viaf/79054878"> אבולעפיה, אברהם בן שמואל</persName>
							</author>
							<note>
								<p>On the authorship of this piece see folio 33r and also  <ref target="Idel_1976" type="page">29</ref>. </p>
							</note>
						</msItem>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="36r" to="54v"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Sefer hamlakhot</title>
							<title xml:lang="he">ספר המלכות</title>
							<author>
								<persName xml:lang="en">Daṿid, ha-Leṿi</persName>
								<persName xml:lang="he">דוד, הלוי</persName>
							</author>
							<note>
								<p>Contains two pieces, which according to Gershom Scholem, in <ref target="Festschrift_Freiman_1935" type="page">66</ref>, belonged together. The first starts on folio 36r, and the second follows beginning with folio 38v.</p>
								<p>See also Scholem's remarks in  <ref target="Kiryat_Sefer_61" type="page">109-110</ref> and <ref target="Idel_1976" type="page">450</ref> note 1 in volume 2.</p>
							</note>
						</msItem>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="55r" to="63r"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Or yakar (fragments)</title>
							<title xml:lang="he">אור יקר (שיה"ש, לקוטים)</title>
							<author>
								<persName xml:lang="en" key="http://viaf.org/viaf/12317536">Cordovero, Moses ben Jacob, 1522-1570</persName>
								<persName xml:lang="he" key="http://viaf.org/viaf/12317536">קורדוברו, משה</persName>
							</author>
							<incipit xml:lang="he">קיצור מועתק מס' זוהר חדש מהרמ"ק על שיר השירים שלוקט ממנו.<locus n="55r"/>
							</incipit>
							<filiation>Cf. <ref target="Neubauer_1994" type="number">2905</ref>.</filiation>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
					<physDesc rend="visible">
						<p>Paper codex of the 16th to the 17th century.</p>
